1.title: Myths & Legends
1.plot: This week's Episode is about Startup Myths and Legends, with award winning tech journalist Kara Swisher and Australia's own startup legend Patrick Llewellyn CEO, 99Designs. Startups include the China Australia Millennial Project (CAMP) connects the innovation ecosystems of China and Australia, Whooska an app to help you find street parking in 5 minutes or less, and Kiddsbay, an online global community where kids can learn new skills to kick start their independence by unleashing their entrepreneurial spirit.

2.title: SpaceTech: there's no fiction in this science
2.plot: Space...not the final frontier. Entrepreneurs are now driving exploration and innovation in a field previously dominated by government. Space tourism, robotics, and nano-satellites are growing area of space investment. Space is a great way to inspire young minds into STEM fields, but will we see human space flight, the stuff of science fiction, in our lifetime?

3.title: Not All money is Equal!
3.plot: This week That Startup Show plunged into the world of startup funding, which has had a huge shakeup of late with the rise of cryptocurrency.

4.title: Bodytech - Turning brilliant bio ideas to booming business
4.plot: In this episode That Startup Show plunged headlong into the world of "bodytech" asking in an age where technology is merging with the body: what does it mean to be human?

5.title: Co-founders, Culture Shocks and Robots
5.plot: This week That Startup Show takes a look at company culture and co-founders - and touches on the brave new world where robots are your new colleagues.

6.title: Turnout & Burnout: When teams implode and swans stop swimming
6.plot: Creative solutions are born from conflict. But is there such a thing as too much conflict? Whether internal or external, struggle has limited value past a certain point. Why does some tension lead to successful pivots and others to epic disasters?

7.title: Disrupting Democracy & Fake News and Truth Telling
7.plot: How can technology disrupt our political system in a useful way? We've seen a lot of political turmoil lately, some people blame technology others praise it as a liberating force. Can technology bring politicians, and the people they represent, together in a way in which they can truly collaborate?

8.title: Ghost Tech: Exploring the world of cyber security, AI and different realities for humans
8.plot: How is invisible technology going to change our relationship to the physical world? We look into what is called "The Fourth Interface," integration in the form of IoT, AR/VR, and holograms into our everyday lives. We also peer into the fascinating world of "ghost tech" where AI, chatbots and cyber security experts work undercover.

9.title: Goodie Tech. Can you make a profit and make a difference?
9.plot: Consumer trends show a growing movement towards conscious buying. Companies that weave a social mission into their operations are becoming the norm. But what's the deal with these "business do-gooders" - does the model work? Are we entering a world of conscious capitalism where consumers demand better from their companies or do we continue to rely on the charity model to fix problems?

10.title: That Startup Show Finale!
10.plot: What does it means to celebrate success? Can Australia overcome its Tall Poppy Syndrome? Join hosts Rae Johnston and Benjamin Law in our Grand Final as we explore what success means in Startup land.

1.title: What the BLEEP Is a Start Up?
1.plot: Some say a "startup" is two teenagers in their parents' garage. Others say it's simply a state of mind. The panel debates the underlying philosophy and concept of what a startup must have. And the first pitchers compete in the Pitchdown.

2.title: Show Me the Money: Putting Adventure Back Into Venture Capital
2.plot: What is "Venture Capital", how does it work, and how can you get your hands on that sweet, sweet cash. We get insights from the panel of experts who have been on both sides of the table to see what makes investors willing to part with their currency.

3.title: Purpose, Passion & People: The Best Capital You'll Ever Raise
3.plot: Ideas are great but you need something to come up with them...people. How do you inspire people from working on laptops in coffee shops to first hire to going global and keep that "startup ethos?" Also the Pitchdown heats up as the competition narrows.

4.title: This Start Up Life
4.plot: The startup lifestyle: it's scary, exhilarating, you have no work/life balance, and it's incredibly rewarding. You could fail epically, or, make billions and change the world; and we find out how those two things go hand in hand.

5.title: The New Breed of CEO & Who's Advising Them
5.plot: CEOs, we think of them as old men in three piece suits, but in startup world that stereotype is discarded like last week's Tinder match. What does it take to run an agile company in a fast evolving tech landscape, and who do you surround yourself with to stay innovative?

6.title: Companies That Change the World
6.plot: "It's no trick to make a lot of money... if what you want to do is make a lot of money," as they say in Citizen Kane. But what about creating something that truly changes the way the world interacts and communicates. How hard is that trick? We find out.

imdb.title: That Startup Show
plot: We find out what it takes to make a great startup as we inspire, engage, and entertain the next generation of tech entrepreneurs and creators.
